  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The advice: &quot;Fill up a handful of sunscreen and spread it all over your body&quot; is used in
      several sun safety campaigns. The hope is that users in swimwear following the advice will
      apply a sunscreen quantity of 2 mg/cm^2 to all accessible skin. The present study is the
      first to investigate how this advice works in practice.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
